b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Maia vs. Shields</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 29</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held on October 9, 2013, at the <a href="/wiki/Gin%C3%A1sio_Jos%C3%A9_Corr%C3%AAa" title="Gin\xc3\xa1sio Jos\xc3\xa9 Corr\xc3\xaaa">Gin\xc3\xa1sio Jos\xc3\xa9 Corr\xc3\xaaa</a> in <a href="/wiki/Barueri" title="Barueri">Barueri</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup> The event was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Fox_Sports_1" title="Fox Sports 1">Fox Sports 1</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event was headlined by a welterweight bout between <a href="/wiki/Demian_Maia" title="Demian Maia">Demian Maia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jake_Shields" title="Jake Shields">Jake Shields</a>,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFCFN29_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFCFN29-4">[4]</a></sup> with the main card broadcast on <a href="/wiki/Fox_Sports_1" title="Fox Sports 1">Fox Sports 1</a>.\n</p>, <p><a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Rony_Jason" title="Rony Jason">Rony Jason</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Jeremy_Stephens" title="Jeremy Stephens">Jeremy Stephens</a> at this event. However, Jason and Stephens both pulled out due to injuries<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup> and the bout was rescheduled for <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night_32" title="UFC Fight Night 32">UFC Fight Night 32</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Rodrigo_Damm" title="Rodrigo Damm">Rodrigo Damm</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Hacran_Dias" title="Hacran Dias">Hacran Dias</a> at the event.  However, the bout was scrapped just days prior to the event after Damm was sidelined due to a <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Kidney_stone" title="Kidney stone">kidney stone</a> attack.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Thiago_Silva_(fighter)" title="Thiago Silva (fighter)">Thiago Silva</a> came in 2\xc2\xa0lbs over the 206\xc2\xa0lbs weight limit and therefore <a href="/wiki/Matt_Hamill" title="Matt Hamill">Matt Hamill</a> received 25% of Silva\'s purse.  Their bout took place at a catchweight of 208\xc2\xa0lbs.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup> Dana White stated Silva would be ineligible for any finishing bonuses, no matter the outcome of the fight, due to his missing weight.\n</p>, <p>Even though he was the only fighter to win by submission on the card, <a href="/wiki/Rousimar_Palhares" title="Rousimar Palhares">Rousimar Palhares</a> was denied the <i>Submission of the Night</i> bonus after holding the submission after <a href="/wiki/Mike_Pierce" title="Mike Pierce">Mike Pierce</a> had tapped, requiring the referee to physically release him. The following day, <a href="/wiki/Dana_White" title="Dana White">Dana White</a> announced that Palhares would be released from his contract and banned from working at UFC ever again.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup> He had done the same at <a href="/wiki/UFC_111" title="UFC 111">UFC 111</a>,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup> earning a 90-day suspension, and was also suspended for nine months after testing positive for elevated testosterone following his loss to <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Hector_Lombard" title="Hector Lombard">Hector Lombard</a> at <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_on_FX:_Sotiropoulos_vs._Pearson" title="UFC on FX: Sotiropoulos vs. Pearson">UFC on FX: Sotiropoulos vs. Pearson</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>]'